hcxtools
------------------------------------------
Small set of tools convert packets from captures (h = hash, c = capture,
convert and calculate candidates, x = different hashtypes) for the use with
latest hashcat or John the Ripper. The tools are 100% compatible to hashcat and
John the Ripper and recommended by hashcat. This branch is pretty closely
synced to hashcat git branch (that means: latest hcxtools matching on latest
hashcat beta) and John the Ripper git branch (bleeding-jumbo).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.4-2
  libcurl4-7.83.0-1
  libssl1.1-1.1.1n-1
  zlib0-1.2.12-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.38-1
  cygport-0.35.0-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  libcurl-devel-7.83.0-1
  libssl-devel-1.1.1n-1
  make-4.3-1
  zlib-devel-1.2.12-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/ZerBea/hcxtools

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/ZerBea/hcxtools/archive/refs/tags/6.2.7.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack hcxtools-6.2.7-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./hcxtools-6.2.7-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/hcxtools-6.2.7-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/hcxtools-6.2.7-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(hcxtools)
  /usr/bin/hcxeiutool.exe
  /usr/bin/hcxessidtool.exe
  /usr/bin/hcxhash2cap.exe
  /usr/bin/hcxhashcattool.exe
  /usr/bin/hcxhashtool.exe
  /usr/bin/hcxmactool.exe
  /usr/bin/hcxpcapngtool.exe
  /usr/bin/hcxpmkidtool.exe
  /usr/bin/hcxpmktool.exe
  /usr/bin/hcxpsktool.exe
  /usr/bin/hcxwltool.exe
  /usr/bin/whoismac.exe
  /usr/bin/wlancap2wpasec.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/hcxtools.README
  /usr/share/doc/hcxtools/LICENSE.txt
  /usr/share/doc/hcxtools/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/hcxtools/changelog
  /usr/share/man/man1/hcxtools.1.gz

